-- Foreign Purchases of Canadian Securities Slowed in December
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2012-02-16T13:30:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/foreign-purchases-of-canadian-securities-slowed-in-december.html
Foreigners slowed their net purchases
of Canadian securities in December led by bonds, capping a year
where the annual total also declined from a record, government
figures showed.  Foreign net purchases of C$7.38 billion ($7.35 billion) in
December trailed November’s revised total of C$14.6 billion,
 Statistics Canada  said today in Ottawa. The annual total also
slowed to C$95.6 billion from C$117.4 billion in 2010, the report
said.  Purchases of bonds fell to C$2.12 billion in December from
C$5.90 billion. Foreign buying of money-market paper was a net
C$3.52 billion, bringing the annual total to a record C$32.0
billion.  Foreigners also bought a net C$1.74 billion of equities in
the month, slowing from November’s purchase of C$3.06 billion.  Canadians  bought  C$2.78 billion of foreign securities in
December, down from C$2.94 billion in November. The annual total
rose to C$17.6 billion from C$14.5 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
